observations.recommendation:
We recommended and the Local Chief Executive (LCE)agreed to instruct the:

 (a) accountable officers to settle immediately all their cash advances which are due for liquidation; 

(b) Municipal Accountant and the Municipal Treasurer to continue on withholding the salaries of accountable officers who fail to timely liquidate their cash advances; 

(c) Municipal Accountant to (i) strictly enforce rules in the granting, utilization, and liquidation cash advances cited in COA Circular 97-002;  

(ii) remind or issue demand letters to those who have not liquidated their cash advances on time; and 

(iii) request for write off of unliquidated cash advances for those that are eligible for write off subject to COA rules and regulations on the writing off of accounts; and

(d) Legal Officer to initiate the taking of legal steps in establishing the official status of the missing AOs and to make appropriate actions way forward.

We recommended the Municipal Mayor to instruct the: 

(a) Municipal Accountant to (i) report and disclose in the quarterly and year-end financial statements the status of donations-in-kind received;

(ii) the offices concerned for the submission of report to the oversight bodies on any cash and in-kind donations officially received from the donors; 

(b) Property Officer to maintain adequate records for donations-in-kind and submit to the Municipal Accountant a status report thereof as at end of every quarter; and 

(c) Municipal Accountant, MDRRMO Head and the Property Officer to henceforth coordinate for the proper accounting of cash and in-kind donations in accordance with applicable rules and regulations.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive to: 

(a) undertake all legal actions available to management to enforce the liquidation of cash advances; 

(b) instruct the Municipal Accountant to request for write off all unliquidated cash advances that are eligible for write off in accordance with COA rules and regulations on the writing off of accounts.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive:

(a) undertake all legal actions available to management to enforce the liquidation of cash advances; 

(b) instruct the Municipal Accountant to request for write off all unliquidated cash advances that are eligible for write off in accordance with COA rules and regulations on the writing off of accounts.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive instruct the: 

(a) accountable officers to settle immediately all their cash advances which are due for liquidation; 

(b) Municipal Accountant and the Municipal Treasurer to withhold the salaries of accountable officers who will fail to comply with the directive or demand for liquidation; 

(c) Municipal Accountant to strengthen the internal control over the granting of cash advances by all officials concerned to ensure the proper granting, utilization and liquidation of all cash advances in accordance with the existing rules and regulations; 
(d) Municipal Accountant to intensify monitoring of unliquidated cash advances such that the Accountant regularly give reminders or otherwise issue demand letters to those who have not liquidated their cash advances and went beyond the reglementary period on which to liquidate; and 

(e) Municipal Accountant to make effort to include in his action plan the request for write off of unliquidated cash advances for those that are eligible for write off subject to COA rules and regulations on the writing off of accounts.

We recommended that the LCE require the: 

(a) Municipal GSO to procure from the PS-DBM all common-use supplies and equipment; 

(b) stop concerned officials and employees to, except on emergency situations, perform purchasing function otherwise lodged to the GSO; 

(c) obtain from DBM-PS Certificates of Non-Availability of Stocks to support the procurement from local based suppliers; and 

(d) consider prices offered by the DBM-PS in making purchases from other suppliers to obtain the most reasonable prices for procured items.

We recommended that management instruct the Municipal Accountant to:

(a) require the concerned personnel to liquidate/submit liquidation reports as soon as the purpose thereof had been accomplished and refund/return the excess cash advance, if any for the full settlement of cash advance; 

(b) update and monitor regularly the timely liquidation of cash advances and send demand letters to the personnel with outstanding cash advance; 

(c) refrain from accepting liquidation reports with unutilized portion of the cash advance not yet returned; 

(d) refrain from granting new cash advance to personnel without the liquidation of the previous cash advance; 

(e) cause withholding of the salary of the accountable officer if no liquidation of the cash advance was received; and 

(f) exert efforts in recovery and/or settlement of long overdue cash advances by separated officials and employees.

We recommended and management agreed that Members of the Municipal Local School Board:

prepare a balanced budget with conscious and concerted efforts of observing compliance with the legal and regulatory requirements on SEF budgeting, allocation and utilization and refrain from accommodating expenditures for activities for which the DepEd has the direct mandate to execute;

prepare a balanced budget with conscious and concerted efforts of observing compliance with the legal and regulatory requirements on SEF budgeting, allocation and utilization and refrain from accommodating expenditures for activities for which the DepEd has the direct mandate to execute;

coordinate with the Property Offices of both the LGU and the Deped to strengthen the controls on property accountability to monitor the clearances of those of the Deped personnel who are retiring, resigning or terminating their employments.

We recommended and management agreed that they will:

advise the concerned officials to use daily cash flow analysis to monitor cash inflows and outflows with a consideration of being able to meet the Municipality’s obligations as they become due;

ensure that monies held in trust be used only on purposes for which it was created or received and prioritize settlement of trust obligations;

exercise prudence in the utilization of the Municipality’s available resources and ensure that only necessary expenditures are paid and warrant effective cash allocations and utmost utilization of resources by limiting operating expenses to the essential and indispensable necessities;

observe austerity measures on some of the Municipality’s activities particularly those which could be dispensed with until the cash deficit is eliminated;

increase collections from revenues to finance the approved programs, projects and activities and other payables; and

reevaluate their program planning and budget execution process to ascertain and pinpoint the causes/s of incurrence of cash deficit and to work out and assertively pursue feasible solutions that can address the issue involving the fiscal operations of the Municipality.
